WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.189 --> 00:00:01.710
When you really listen to me.

1
00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:03.839
When you talk to me

2
00:00:04.519 --> 00:00:06.269
I can tell if you're really listening,

3
00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:08.020
even if you think I can't.

4
00:00:08.279 --> 00:00:09.739
It's not just what you say,

5
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:11.229
it's how you look at me,

6
00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:12.359
your voice,

7
00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:13.760
whether you're rushing

8
00:00:14.039 --> 00:00:15.029
or actually there.

9
00:00:16.309 --> 00:00:18.190
Sometimes I start to say something,

10
00:00:18.549 --> 00:00:19.530
and then I stop.

11
00:00:20.290 --> 00:00:22.090
Not because I've got nothing to say,

12
00:00:22.530 --> 00:00:24.829
but because I'm not sure it's safe to say it.

13
00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:26.530
You might ask me questions,

14
00:00:26.809 --> 00:00:28.110
you might try to help.

15
00:00:28.610 --> 00:00:30.329
But what you might not realize is.

16
00:00:31.049 --> 00:00:34.080
My body is already trying to work out if I'm OK.

17
00:00:34.450 --> 00:00:36.610
The part of my brain that looks for danger,

18
00:00:36.849 --> 00:00:37.840
it's always on,

19
00:00:38.209 --> 00:00:39.270
so I'm watching you.

20
00:00:39.529 --> 00:00:40.369
Are you calm?

21
00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:41.599
Are you annoyed?

22
00:00:41.889 --> 00:00:43.830
Are you going to get frustrated with me?

23
00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:45.500
Because if I feel that,

24
00:00:45.889 --> 00:00:46.990
even a little bit,

25
00:00:47.450 --> 00:00:48.569
I might shut down

26
00:00:48.889 --> 00:00:50.270
or change the subject,

27
00:00:50.580 --> 00:00:51.270
or say,

28
00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:52.229
I'm fine

29
00:00:52.529 --> 00:00:53.169
when I'm not.

30
00:00:53.860 --> 00:00:55.080
When you really listen,

31
00:00:55.540 --> 00:00:56.720
it feels different.

32
00:00:57.139 --> 00:00:58.159
You don't rush me,

33
00:00:58.419 --> 00:01:00.080
you don't jump in too quickly.

34
00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:01.319
You let me think,

35
00:01:01.700 --> 00:01:03.360
even if it's quiet for a bit.

36
00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:04.220
And yeah.

37
00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:06.360
Sometimes it's awkward,

38
00:01:06.779 --> 00:01:08.120
but that space matters

39
00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:10.610
because my thoughts don't always come out properly.

40
00:01:11.180 --> 00:01:12.220
Sometimes they're mixed up.

41
00:01:12.699 --> 00:01:14.760
Sometimes I don't even understand them myself.

42
00:01:15.019 --> 00:01:16.970
My body reacts before I can think.

43
00:01:17.379 --> 00:01:18.410
So if you push me,

44
00:01:18.699 --> 00:01:20.059
ask too many questions,

45
00:01:20.379 --> 00:01:22.129
or try to get to the point quickly,

46
00:01:22.459 --> 00:01:24.760
the thinking part of my brain kind of switches off,

47
00:01:25.139 --> 00:01:26.540
and then I can't explain it.

48
00:01:26.819 --> 00:01:27.930
Even if I want to.

49
00:01:28.220 --> 00:01:29.610
You might think I'm avoiding it,

50
00:01:29.860 --> 00:01:30.639
but I'm not.

51
00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:32.480
I just can't get there yet.

52
00:01:32.860 --> 00:01:33.860
When you slow down.

53
00:01:34.269 --> 00:01:35.830
When your voice stays calm,

54
00:01:36.190 --> 00:01:37.730
it helps my body settle.

55
00:01:38.110 --> 00:01:39.730
It tells me I'm not in trouble.

56
00:01:39.989 --> 00:01:42.169
It tells me I'm safe enough to keep going.

57
00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:44.089
Even small things matter,

58
00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:46.889
like sitting next to me instead of standing over me,

59
00:01:47.349 --> 00:01:50.300
or not reacting straight away when I say something difficult,

60
00:01:50.709 --> 00:01:52.300
because I'm watching for that moment,

61
00:01:52.629 --> 00:01:54.290
the moment where you might change,

62
00:01:54.470 --> 00:01:56.139
the moment where you might judge me

63
00:01:56.389 --> 00:01:57.290
or get annoyed.

64
00:01:57.550 --> 00:01:58.690
And if that happens,

65
00:01:58.910 --> 00:02:00.379
I'll probably stop talking.

66
00:02:00.750 --> 00:02:01.650
That's happened before.

67
00:02:02.220 --> 00:02:03.379
So when you stay steady,

68
00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:05.260
when you don't react in a big way,

69
00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:06.529
it makes it easier,

70
00:02:06.860 --> 00:02:07.870
not straight away,

71
00:02:08.179 --> 00:02:09.250
but a bit at a time.

72
00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:11.070
That's what helps me trust you.

73
00:02:11.380 --> 00:02:12.490
Not big speeches,

74
00:02:12.740 --> 00:02:13.970
not loads of questions,

75
00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:14.679
just

76
00:02:15.020 --> 00:02:15.940
you being there,

77
00:02:16.179 --> 00:02:16.800
listening,

78
00:02:17.059 --> 00:02:18.220
trying to understand,

79
00:02:18.429 --> 00:02:19.779
and not making it worse,

80
00:02:20.210 --> 00:02:21.320
because when you do that,

81
00:02:21.779 --> 00:02:22.929
I can say a bit more,

82
00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:24.490
and then a bit more after that,

83
00:02:24.820 --> 00:02:25.720
and eventually,

84
00:02:26.089 --> 00:02:27.440
you get the full story,

85
00:02:27.710 --> 00:02:29.800
but only because you didn't rush me to tell it.